data.only-css#Only CSS:
To change theme only with CSS you can use prefers-color-scheme media query.
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    body {
        background: black;
        color: white;
    }
}
To set only dark theme for your website you can use color-scheme attribute on root element.
Mozilla color-scheme docs: MDN docs
:root {
    color-scheme: dark; /* or light */
}
To set system theme you can use color-scheme attribute on root element.It will apply dark when your system has dark theme and light when your system has light theme.
:root {
    color-scheme: light dark;
}

